meta-facebook?  This isn't a change in openbmc/openbmc.

Maybe "fby35:"?
In the latest patchset, this has not been resolved.  It still shows meta-facebook instead of meta-greatlakes in the title.

Hi All,
please review the patch and provide your suggestions.
Thanks
Please resolve the sensor names and post code issues raised.
Patrick's comment from an early set has not been addressed.
Where are the other sensors?  Please see issue #72 for a link to the common sensor names needed for greatlakes.

Hi Michel,
         I have added some sensors in this JSON, and referred that issue #72 in this file lot of sensors are there and I can't identify the common sensor here. could you please suggest common sensors name for the great lake?

Can you give more details on what you are asking for?  Some sensors such as the DIMMs have been renumbered as part of the new sensor naming spec for YV3.5/GreatLakes.  For instance, DIMMA_TEMP is now MB_DIMMA0_TEMP_C, DIMMC_TEMP is now MB_DIMMA2_TEMP_C, etc.  Are there other sensors which you do not have a mapping for?
I have mapped other sensors as well, as per the document(BIC Voltage Sensors, BIC Power Sensors as like all sensors) incase if needed other sensors we can add them in the future.

This is minor and I can fix before submitting if this is the only comment, but it is just "greatlakes".  You should only have "meta-*" on a commit in 'openbmc/openbmc'.
Please remove the comment lines throughout this file.  They do not provide anything adding them to the .json file, but add clutter.

In patchset num:7 you have given a comment that is to add (comment on each phase like "Need to add a comment this is UPI Phase - Start" and "Need to add a comment this is UPI Phase - End") that's why I did this, if it is not fine we can go with how other platforms are mentioned in fb-ipmi-oem (ex:yv2 https://github.com/openbmc/fb-ipmi-oem/blob/master/configs/yosemitev2/post_desc.json) is this fine?

The comments to add the phrases was before I realized these were json files.  I was trying to keep some of the comments from our Meta codebase that were applicable, but those don't make sense in a json file as you added them.  Thus, the follow-on request was to remove them and not include any comment lines in the json file.

Looking at the link you provided, I would like us to do something like that for Great Lakes so we don't lose the context around the settings.
